SIMPLE: apparitor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Apparitor
<hw>Ap*par"i*tor</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>apparere</ets>. See <er>Appear</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Formerly, an officer who attended magistrates and judges to execute
their orders.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Before any of his <qex>apparitors</qex> could execute the
sentence, he was himself summoned away by a sterner <qex>apparitor</qex>
to the other world.</q> <rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A messenger or officer who serves
the process of an ecclesiastical court.</def>
<rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Appaume</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
